import React, { Component } from 'react';
import './App.css';
import Movie from './Movie'

const movieTitles = [
  "Matrix",
  "Full Metal Jacket",
  "Old Boys",
  "Star Wars"
]

const movieImages = [
  "data:image/jpeg;base64,",
  "https://images2.minutemediacdn.com/image/upload/c_crop,h_2132,w_3794,x_0,y_22/f_auto,q_auto,w_1100/v1555155644/shape/mentalfloss/full-metal-jacket-hed.jpg",
  "https://i.ytimg.com/vi/N36z1-WzUvk/maxresdefault.jpg",
  "data:image/jpeg;base64,"
]

class App extends Component {
  render() {
    return (
      <div className="App">
        <Movie title={movieTitles[0]} poster={movieImages[0]}></Movie>
        <Movie title={movieTitles[1]} poster={movieImages[1]}></Movie>
        <Movie title={movieTitles[2]} poster={movieImages[2]}></Movie>
        <Movie title={movieTitles[3]} poster={movieImages[3]}></Movie>
      </div>
    );
  }
}
export default App;
